In 2005 while working for the original McGill family business, The North Rocks Greenery, Jon recognised an opportunity. He took on his first Garden Maintenance customer armed with just a pair of secateurs. This idea grew into a thriving local business and expanded to landscaping.

So, when Jon's father moved into retirement, selling the nursery side of the business, Jon, and his wife Bel, took on that side of the business under a new nameLooking Up Landscapes. Originally providing mainly Garden Maintenance to the Hills district of Sydney, as The North Rocks Greenery, the Business was forced to re-brand and re-invent itself following the sale of the Nursery side of the business. Despite the many challenges the reinvention turned into a blessing as the McGill Family business retained the majority of the original customer base in the change and rapidly grew within 18 short months to incorporate more extensive Landscaping services and a strong presence in the Central Coast and Newcastle Market.
